org.apache.ambari.server.security.authentication.kerberos

Class AmbariKerberosAuthenticationProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ambari.server.security.authentication.kerberos.AmbariKerberosAuthenticationProvider
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.springframework.beans.factory.InitializingBean, org.springframework.security.authentication.AuthenticationProvider

    public class AmbariKerberosAuthenticationProvider
extends Object
implements org.springframework.security.authentication.AuthenticationProvider, org.springframework.beans.factory.InitializingBean
    AmbariKerberosAuthenticationProvider is an AuthenticationProvider implementation used to authenticate users using a Kerberos ticket.

    In order for this provider to be usable, Kerberos authentication must be enabled. This may be done using the ambari-server setup-kerberos CLI.

    This implementation supports Trusted Proxy authentication.
